warning[W10010]: module in 'tests/' is not annotated '#[test_only]'
  ┌─ tests/move_check/attributes/test_sources_dir/missing_test_only_warns.move:4:8
  │
4 │ module a::missing_test_only_warns {
  │        ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ Module 'a::missing_test_only_warns' is in 'tests/' but is not annotated '#[test_only]'
  │
  = Modules placed under 'tests/' should be annotated '#[test_only]' (or contain only '#[test]' items). Annotate the module, move it out of 'tests/', or suppress with '#[allow(tests_missing_test_only)]'.
  = This warning can be suppressed with '#[allow(tests_missing_test_only)]' applied to the 'module' or module member ('const', 'fun', or 'struct')
